{
  "_comment": [
    "Brand knowledge that used to live in Java (VinBrandDetector WMI rules,",
    "DtcReader ECU-name maps and enhanced-mode switches).",
    "",
    "WMI matching is LONGEST-PREFIX-WINS. That is what removes the old",
    "hand-ordered if-chain, where a broad rule placed above a specific one made",
    "the specific rule unreachable dead code (editing it changed nothing).",
    "'JTH' beats 'JT'; 'MNT' beats 'MN'; 'LGX' beats 'LG'. Order here is",
    "irrelevant, so adding a brand cannot break an existing one.",
    "",
    "This is a single file rather than one per brand on purpose: WMI collisions",
    "are inherently cross-brand, and splitting them across 38 files would hide",
    "exactly the conflicts that caused the original bug. Per-brand DTC code",
    "definitions stay in their own dtc_<brand>.json files.",
    "",
    "Shipped via the same OTA channel as the DTC databases (dtc_updates/",
    "manifest.json), so a new brand needs no app release.",
    "",
    "ecu_names keys are CAN IDs in hex. enhanced_modes are 'request,response'",
    "mode pairs for manufacturer-specific DTC reads."
  ],
